Currently the JIRA Issues Macro in Confluence, does not accept manually added parameters to the xml of a search query/filter as described in [this|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA043/Displaying+Search+Results+in+XML] documentation. The data does get changed when you follow the xml itself after adding parameters, but the macro seems to ignore them.

Only the default out of the box defined columns are used in the xml and interpreted by the macro, changes made to the displayed columns of a filter's result, are not taken into consideration when creating the xml. In addition to that, in case a customer uses custom fields, and wants to display these through the macro, the customer has define all columns separately to get them displayed.

